Great movie. Great story. Great music. I loved this vampire tale. Made me laugh, made me think and and made me cringe. Excellently directed and excellent score.

Trailer:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=qWRlq__5iRo</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/TFKOO4H.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Let the Right One In
 
Probably my favorite vampire movie. The movie is a sad story with excellent directing and beautiful yet dark undertones. 

Trailer:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ZonUW_acsOg</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1cvdY3S.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>What We Do In The Shadows
  
Hilarious. A great comedy of roommates who are vampires coping with everyday life. A must see!

Trailer:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=HUPhDTG70f8</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ztLiGvz.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Thirst
 
One of the best stories I have seen in a vampire move. It is a long one but worth it. Very deep and dark with brooding elements. 

Trailer:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ODoagpV68gA</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1Z7vP4G.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Dracula: Dead and Loving It
 
Classic. Mel Brooks and Leslie are amazing in this comedy vampire flick. A must see if you are into the slapstick humor. 

Trailer:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=tVdn8JH91Dg</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/T5eiPUt.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The Lost Boys

After moving to a new town, two brothers are convinced that the area is frequented by vampires.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zDQ0_lXClxc</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/iUYICuF.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>30 Days of Night
 
Though one of the larger marketed films, I still found it quite intriguing and creepy. Great depiction of the vampires! 

Trailer:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=fOFsXrEc8Oc</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GaaytXh.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Byzantium
 
Mother and daughter vampires move to a home to try and cope with their vampness. Pretty darn good in all aspects. 

Trailer:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=Dj1yxdhJNqA</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/pqXSEom.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>A Girl Walks Home Alone At Night 

Never seen a vampire movie like this one. Very arthouse (which I like). Excellent cinematography and music. A must see if you are tired of the usual vampire flick.

Trailer:
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9PLm4ecu25o</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/q61WEJb.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Nosferatu
